   users under the same AGPL license.

2. MODIFICATIONS: Any modifications you make must also be licensed under AGPL
   and the source code must be made available.

3. NETWORK USE: Unlike GPL, AGPL requires source code disclosure even when
   the software is used to provide a network service (SaaS).

4. ATTRIBUTION: You must preserve all copyright notices and license information.

5. PATENT GRANTS: Contributors grant patent licenses for their contributions.

